cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the problem of searching and resolving identities of users across multiple social networks. It involves techniques from social informatics (cs.SI) to understand how users create and manage their identities on social networks, information retrieval (cs.IR) to search for relevant information across multiple networks, computational linguistics (cs.CL) to analyze the content of user profiles and connections, cybersecurity (cs.CY) to ensure the privacy and security of user data, and multimedia (cs.MM) to handle different types of content such as text, images, and videos.
